scenario: Generate pricing for an AI meeting-notes app
given:
  app_name: "Briefly"
  target_customer: "Remote product teams"
  value_metric: "processed meeting"
  monthly_value_units_per_customer: 40
  active_customers: 500
  fixed_monthly_cost: 1200
  gross_margin_target: 75
  paid_conversion: 8
  monthly_growth: 12
  monthly_churn: 4
  cost_drivers:
    - label: "LLM transcription and summary"
      unit_label: "meeting"
      cost_per_unit: 0.18
      units_per_customer_month: 40
    - label: "Storage"
      unit_label: "GB"
      cost_per_unit: 0.04
      units_per_customer_month: 2
when:
  the founder runs the pricing engine
then:
  - the app generates at least four tiers
  - paid tiers have positive monthly prices
  - the free tier has a usage cap
  - each paid tier has an overage policy
  - the simulation includes revenue, COGS, gross margin, and break-even status
  - the billing summary contains metering events

scenario: Switch demo presets
given:
  the judge is viewing the default Briefly preset
when:
  the judge selects another demo preset
then:
  - the app name, product summary, target customer, value metric, assumptions, and cost drivers update
  - generated tiers recalculate for the selected app
  - Claude and FLock refinements are cleared because the assumptions changed
  - the preset options include meeting notes, coding assistant, media generation, and support automation examples

scenario: Flag risky free tier
given:
  variable_cost_per_customer: high
  free_tier_allowance: high
when:
  audit runs
then:
  - free-tier abuse risk is visible
  - recommendation includes reducing allowance, adding verification, or moving heavy actions behind credits

scenario: Explain Solvimon fit
given:
  generated pricing output
when:
  judge opens the billing summary
then:
  - the summary names usage-based pricing
  - the summary names hybrid pricing when seats and usage both matter
  - the summary lists billing events and invoice line items
  - the Solvimon Handoff tab shows a Solvimon import preview
  - the preview shows meter count, plan count, invoice line count, and credit policy count
  - the preview JSON contains meters, plans, invoice_items, credit_policies, and implementation_notes
  - the handoff shows a compact developer billing object before the full JSON
  - Copy import JSON copies the same JSON payload shown in the preview
  - Download JSON saves the same JSON payload shown in the preview

scenario: Use demo mode during judging
given:
  the founder is preparing the live presentation
when:
  the founder turns on Demo mode
then:
  - the intake form is hidden
  - the visible tabs are Pricing, Solvimon Handoff, Revenue Simulation, Startup Case, and Submission Pack
  - Previous and Next controls move through the presentation route
  - the pricing score strip remains visible
  - the founder can exit demo mode without losing the current pricing assumptions

scenario: Stress-test pricing assumptions
given:
  generated pricing output
when:
  judge opens the Simulation tab
then:
  - the app shows model-cost shock, usage spike, conversion drop, and churn rise scenarios
  - each scenario shows month-12 revenue, revenue delta, gross margin, margin delta, audit score, and break-even month
  - a model-cost shock increases month-12 COGS compared with the base case

scenario: Claude refinement with missing key
given:
  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is not configured
when:
  founder clicks Claude refine
then:
  - the deterministic pricing model remains visible
  - the app explains that ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is not configured
  - the API response includes a stable CONFIGURATION_ERROR code and request id
  - no pricing inputs are lost

scenario: Claude refinement with configured key
given:
  ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is configured
when:
  founder clicks Claude refine
then:
  - the app calls the server-side refinement endpoint
  - the endpoint uses the Vercel AI SDK for structured generation
  - the API key is never exposed to the browser
  - the response focuses on Solvimon and Codeplain
  - the response includes pricing rationale, Solvimon implementation notes, Codeplain next steps, suggested changes, and risks

scenario: Explain business potential
given:
  judge opens the Startup Case tab
when:
  Priceplain renders the submission story
then:
  - the customer is a founder building an AI-native app
  - the problem is variable AI usage cost and unclear monetisation
  - the product wedge is pricing before billing implementation
  - the revenue path is credible for a self-serve founder tool
  - the Solvimon and Codeplain fit are visible without reading the README

scenario: Sovereign AI Review without FLock key
given:
  FLOCK_API_KEY is not configured
when:
  judge opens the Sovereign tab
then:
  - the app shows deterministic governance scoring
  - the app shows data sovereignty, usage auditability, vendor lock-in, commercial transparency, and public-sector suitability
  - the app shows procurement questions and governance actions
  - the app explains the suggested FLock-compatible inference path

scenario: FLock review with missing key
given:
  FLOCK_API_KEY is not configured
when:
  founder clicks FLock review
then:
  - the deterministic sovereign review remains visible
  - the app explains that FLOCK_API_KEY is not configured
  - the API response includes a stable CONFIGURATION_ERROR code and request id
  - no pricing or governance inputs are lost

scenario: Sovereign AI Review with FLock key
given:
  FLOCK_API_KEY is configured
when:
  founder clicks FLock review
then:
  - the app calls the server-side sovereign review endpoint
  - the endpoint calls FLock's OpenAI-compatible API using a server-side key
  - the API key is never exposed to the browser
  - the response focuses on UK sovereign AI, governance, auditability, privacy, institutional procurement, and data ownership

scenario: Export final submission artefact
given:
  judge opens the Submission Pack tab
when:
  Priceplain renders the final export view
then:
  - the pricing-page preview is visible
  - the preset comparison is visible
  - the Solvimon Judge Lens explains demand, monetisation, differentiation, post-hackathon plan, and demo tone
  - track coverage for Solvimon, Codeplain, Vercel, and FLock is visible
  - the demo script is visible
  - the submission checklist is visible
  - the full report text is visible as a fallback export artefact
  - Copy report includes pricing, metering, Solvimon import preview, sensitivity checks, provider status, sovereign review, Solvimon judge lens, track coverage, demo script, and checklist
  - Download Markdown saves the same report text as a markdown file

scenario: Follow optional Solvimon checkout guide
given:
  a founder wants to turn the Priceplain handoff into a test checkout page
when:
  the founder reads docs/SOLVIMON_CHECKOUT_GUIDE.md
then:
  - the guide explains how to create and activate a Solvimon test sandbox
  - the guide explains where to create a Solvimon test API key
  - the guide explains how to configure the Solvimon MCP server
  - the guide includes a prompt for creating meters, plans and a checkout link
  - the guide explains where to find the Solvimon checkout pages area
  - the guide includes test-card details and warns not to use real payment cards
  - the guide states that Priceplain itself does not process payments

scenario: Check live provider readiness
given:
  judge asks whether live AI calls are configured
when:
  Priceplain loads
then:
  - the app calls the provider-status endpoint
  - Claude key status is visible
  - FLock key status is visible
  - key values are never exposed to the browser
  - the status endpoint does not call external providers

scenario: Shareable demo sections
given:
  judge is viewing the default Pricing tab
when:
  judge opens Startup Case, Sovereign, Revenue Simulation, Solvimon Handoff, or Submission Pack
then:
  - the browser URL updates with the selected tab
  - reloading the URL opens the same selected tab
  - using browser back or forward restores the matching tab
  - an invalid tab query falls back to Pricing

scenario: Smoke-test live demo contract
given:
  the local dev server is running
when:
  the builder runs npm run smoke
then:
  - the home app shell returns successfully
  - shareable Business and Sovereign URLs return the app shell
  - priceplan and sovereign-review reject GET requests with METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED
  - provider-status accepts GET requests
  - priceplan and sovereign-review reject empty payloads with VALIDATION_ERROR
  - sovereign-review rejects invalid JSON with INVALID_JSON
  - every API error response includes a request id

scenario: Test deterministic domain logic
given:
  the project dependencies are installed
when:
  the builder runs npm run test:domain
then:
  - every demo preset produces at least four tiers
  - paid tiers have overage rates
  - Solvimon preview schema, meters, plans, base subscription line items, and overage line items are present
  - sensitivity scenarios are present
  - the model-cost shock scenario increases month-12 COGS
  - sovereign review produces governance signals

scenario: Browser-render judge routes
given:
  the local dev server is running
when:
  the builder runs npm run test:browser
then:
  - the home route renders the Priceplain shell
  - the Solvimon Handoff route renders the Solvimon import preview
  - the Solvimon Handoff route renders the value metric, meter events, plans, invoice items and JSON export pipeline
  - the Solvimon Handoff route renders Copy import JSON and Download JSON controls
  - the Revenue Simulation route renders sensitivity checks
  - the Submission Pack route renders preset comparison and Markdown download
  - the Submission Pack route renders the Solvimon Judge Lens
  - the Submission Pack route renders Why Priceplain stands out
  - the Startup Case route renders the tightened pitch
  - the Sovereign route renders the FLock-aligned governance view
